title: Baltimore police can't confirm Carson's story of holdup
text: > Top News Baltimore police can't confirm Carson's story of holdup In this photo taken Oct. 9, 2015, Republican presidential candidate Dr. Ben Carson speaks at the National Press Club in Washington. The Baltimore Police Department said Tuesday that it canâ€™t verify, without any additional information, that Carson was once held at gunpoint at a fast-food restaurant in the city. Carson, a retired Johns Hopkins Hospital neurosurgeon, told Sirius XM Radio last Wednesday he was in a Popeyes restaurant while working as a doctor in Baltimore. (AP Photo/Andrew Harnik)
